          "description": "Finding a clean and accessible restroom in Manhattan can be a challenge, but this spot is a hidden gem. Located right next to Black Fox Coffee, it's easy to miss if you're not paying attention. The entrance is an unmarked door, but there's a security guard nearby who can point you in the right direction. The restroom is all-gender, which is a plus for inclusivity, and it's surprisingly clean\u2014almost spotless compared to many other public restrooms I've encountered in the city. The fact that it's well-maintained and easily accessible makes it a lifesaver when you're out and about in Midtown. Highly recommend if you're in the area and in need of a quick break.",
